{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}} {{Use Indian English|date=January 2016}} {{Infobox religious building | religious_affiliation = [[Jainism]] | image = Upper Temple Complex at Tirumalai.jpg | image_size = 300px | alt = Upper Temple Complex at [[Tirumalai (Jain complex)|Tirumalai]] | caption = Upper Temple Complex at [[Tirumalai (Jain complex)|Tirumalai]] | map_type = | map_size = | map_alt = Arahanthgiri Jain Math | map_caption = Location within Tamil | coordinates = {{coord|12.22|79.07|display=inline,title}} | location = [[Tiruvannaamalai]], [[Tiruvannamalai district]], [[Tamil Nadu]] | deity = [[Neminatha]] | festivals = [[Mahavir Jayanti]] | temple_quantity = 4 | established = 322–185 BCE | bhattaraka = Swasti Shri Dhavalakeerthi Swami | governing_body = Acharya Shri Akalanka Educational Trust | website = {{url|http://www.akalanka-educational-trust.com}} }} {{Jainism}} '''Arahanthgiri Jain Math''' is a [[Jain Matha]] that established near [[Tirumalai (Jain complex)|Tirumalai]] in August, 1998.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jainheritagecentres.com/index.php/donations/to-jain-tirths/111-arihantagiri-tirumalai |title=Arihantagiri - Tirumalai |accessdate=April 10, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121107091818/http://www.jainheritagecentres.com/index.php/donations/to-jain-tirths/111-arihantagiri-tirumalai |archivedate=7 November 2012 }}</ref> The Math is headed by [[Bhattaraka Dhavalakeerthi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/2004/05/02/stories/2004050200890300.htm |title=Karnataka / Shimoga News : `Society should pay obeisance to guru peethas' |publisher=The Hindu |date=2004-05-02 |accessdate=2012-05-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.deccanherald.com/content/Apr122008/district2008041162196.asp |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120708210444/http://archive.deccanherald.com/content/Apr122008/district2008041162196.asp |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2012-07-08 |title=Deccan Herald - Bimba shuddhi begins |publisher=Archive.deccanherald.com |date= |accessdate=2012-05-26 }}</ref>
==History== History of Arahanthgiri Jain Math starts from the period of 322–185 BCE as the Last ‘Shrutkevali’ Bhadrabahu expected to stay at this place. He stayed at this place to practice meditation and “Swadhyaya” along with 8000 other saints. The Village Thirumalai where this Jain Math is located is also known as Arhatsugiri or Arihantgiri.<ref>http://www.yatrastotemples.com/arahanthgiri-jain-math-in-thirumalai/</ref> This more than 2,000 years old temple is near Tirumala. The complex is now managed by [[Archaeological Survey of India]].<ref>https://richardarunachala.wordpress.com/2014/09/30/ancient-jain-temple-complex-near-tiruvannamalai/</ref><ref>http://www.exploremytrip.com/location-details/info/MTk2NjE/Arihant-Giri-Digambar-Jain-Temple</ref>
==Main Temple== We can find the 16 meter Neminath Idol on the top of the hill having 140 steps at this location.This idol is believed to be dated as old as 12th century. A very famous south Indian movie has been shot around the theme of Neminatha. We can see various ancient caves existing in this Jain Math along with 16 meter idol of Neminath and hundreds of Religious books.
