The '''Gharami''' are [[Hindu]] [[Caste system in India|caste]] found in the state of [[Uttar Pradesh]], India. Their traditional occupation was thatching and lattice work.their customs are similar to other [[North India]]n Hindus.{{cn|date=February 2017}} In Uttar Pradesh, they have been granted [[Scheduled Caste]] status and at the [[2011 Census of India]] numbered 37 people in 12 households.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/PCA/SC_ST/PCA-A10/SC-0900-PCA-A-10-ddw.xlsx |title= A-10 Individual Scheduled Caste Primary Census Abstract Data and its Appendix - Uttar Pradesh |publisher=Registrar General & Census Commissioner, India |accessdate=2017-02-04}}</ref>

